# Select + Do — Web App Reference (Authoritative Parity Spec)

## Product pillars
- Single loop: **Add → Find → Focus → Review**.
- **Modes**: Work | Personal (exact labels).
- Time brackets: 5, 10, 15, 20, 25, 30, 45, 60 + Custom.
- Tasks: Atomic | Standard | Progress. Optional Priority.

## Global UI tokens
- Section rhythm: **32 px** between blocks; internal spacing 12 px.
- Card: radius 16; 1 px border (neutral/12%); soft shadow.
- Chip: pill, med font, 8/12 padding; selected = filled accent.
- Palette (semantic):
  - Accent = Blue (buttons, selected chips)
  - Surface = Background (grouped)
  - Border = Quaternary
  - Positive = Green; Warning = Orange
- Icons: SF Symbol analogs on iOS.

## Primary flows (acceptance criteria)
### Find
1) “What Mode Are You In?” → chips: **Work, Personal**.
2) “How Much Time Do You Have?” → chips: 5–60 + **Custom**.
3) “Pick a Task” → task cards (title, kind, context, minutes, optional star).
4) Row actions under time:
   - Priority Only (toggle)
   - Reset (context=Personal, time=15, priority=false)
   - Reshuffle (randomize list)
5) Advanced Filters (collapsed by default) includes: Energy, Projects, Tags (not required for first iOS cut).

### Add
- Fields: Title, Context (Work/Personal), Type (Atomic/Standard/Progress), Minutes list, Priority toggle.
- Full-width **Add Task** primary button.

### Focus
- Modal/sheet timer with task title + selected time; Pause, Stop/Discard, Mark Complete.

### Review
- Completed Today list (title + minutes).
- Weekly Insights:
  - Most productive context (mode)
  - Preferred time bracket (Quick 5–15, Standard 20–30, Long 45–60)
  - “Haven’t touched” suggestions (optional later)
  - “Most time spent on Progress” (optional later)

## Data model (web)
```json
{
  "id": "uuid",
  "title": "string",
  "context": "Work|Personal",
  "kind": "Atomic|Standard|Progress",
  "minutes": 5|10|15|20|25|30|45|60,
  "isPriority": true|false,
  "completedAt": "timestamp|null",
  "updatedAt": "timestamp"
}